---
/**
 * advanced-ai-systems/0001 · Figure 3 — "Orchestrator-worker vs swarm" (Module 2).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/advanced-ai-systems/lessons/0001-multi-agent-systems-
 * when-and-when-not.html. Uses shared arrowhead markers #arwG and #arwR (defined
 * by <Fig0>), incl. marker-start on the swarm's bidirectional edges. Kept as an
 * .astro component (not inline MDX) for reliable raw-SVG rendering. SVG anchor id
 * (r3b) matches the source DOM + the #s2 footnote.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Orchestrator-worker has a lead agent that fans out to workers and synthesizes results; a swarm has peer agents with no central planner coordinating through shared state."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Orchestrator-worker vs swarm</text
        >

        <!-- orchestrator-worker -->
        <rect
            x="30"
            y="34"
            width="270"
            height="180"
            rx="10"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="165" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Orchestrator-worker</text
        >
        <rect x="120" y="62" width="90" height="28" rx="6" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="165" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >lead (plans)</text
        >
        <line x1="140" y1="90" x2="90" y2="118" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <line x1="165" y1="90" x2="165" y2="118" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <line x1="190" y1="90" x2="240" y2="118" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <rect x="55" y="120" width="62" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text x="86" y="137" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#111110"
            >worker</text
        >
        <rect x="134" y="120" width="62" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text x="165" y="137" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#111110"
            >worker</text
        >
        <rect x="213" y="120" width="62" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text x="244" y="137" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#111110"
            >worker</text
        >
        <line x1="86" y1="146" x2="150" y2="170" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <line x1="165" y1="146" x2="165" y2="170" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <line x1="244" y1="146" x2="180" y2="170" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <rect x="110" y="172" width="110" height="26" rx="6" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="165" y="189" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >lead synthesizes</text
        >
        <text x="165" y="210" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >one control point · auditable · debuggable</text
        >

        <!-- swarm -->
        <rect
            x="340"
            y="34"
            width="270"
            height="180"
            rx="10"
            fill="#f6eef7"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="475" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Swarm (no lead)</text
        >
        <circle cx="420" cy="95" r="16" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#b5179e"></circle><text
            x="420"
            y="98"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7"
            fill="#111110">peer</text
        >
        <circle cx="530" cy="95" r="16" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#b5179e"></circle><text
            x="530"
            y="98"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7"
            fill="#111110">peer</text
        >
        <circle cx="420" cy="160" r="16" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#b5179e"></circle><text
            x="420"
            y="163"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7"
            fill="#111110">peer</text
        >
        <circle cx="530" cy="160" r="16" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#b5179e"></circle><text
            x="530"
            y="163"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7"
            fill="#111110">peer</text
        >
        <line
            x1="436"
            y1="95"
            x2="514"
            y2="95"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"
            marker-start="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line
            x1="420"
            y1="111"
            x2="420"
            y2="144"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"
            marker-start="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line
            x1="530"
            y1="111"
            x2="530"
            y2="144"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"
            marker-start="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line
            x1="434"
            y1="106"
            x2="516"
            y2="149"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"
            marker-start="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <text x="475" y="127" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f">shared state</text
        >
        <text x="475" y="196" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >behavior emerges</text
        >
        <text x="475" y="210" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >max parallelism · hard to attribute failures</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Orchestrator-worker gives you a <em>place to stand</em>: one planner, one synthesizer, one
        spot to validate and attribute failures. A swarm trades that control for emergence — great
        for exploration, risky for production.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r3b">3</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
